  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to tinyxxd</title>

    <para>
      The tinyxxd package provides a drop-in replacement for Vim's hexdump
      utility, xxd. This standalone implementation is more modern and performant
      than Vim's.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download: <ulink url="&tinyxxd-download;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of tinyxxd</title>

    <para>
      Install tinyxxd by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>install -vDm755 tinyxxd -t /usr/bin/              &amp;&amp;
ln -sfv tinyxxd /usr/bin/xxd                      &amp;&amp;
install -vDm644 tinyxxd.1 -t /usr/share/man/man1/ &amp;&amp;
ln -sfv tinyxxd.1 /usr/share/man/man1/xxd.1</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

